# Parkinson's disease  

---

## Clinical picture; genetics (35)

**PD patients often have additional symptoms and degeneration**  
* [PubMed abstract of Braak & del Tredici, Neurology 2008](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/18474848) not open-access  
* Braak H, Del Tredici K. Invited Article: Nervous system pathology in sporadic Parkinson disease. Neurology. 2008 May 13;70(20):1916-25. doi:
10.1212/01.wnl.0000312279.49272.9f. Review. PubMed PMID: 18474848.  


---  

## Pathophysiology; non-human models (36)

**Parkinson’s disease: pathophysiology**
* [Wang et al, Eur J Epidemiol. 2011](http://link.springer.com/content/pdf/10.1007%2Fs10654-011-9574-5) open-access [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21505849) 
* Wang A, Costello S, Cockburn M, Zhang X, Bronstein J, Ritz B. Parkinson's disease risk from ambient exposure to pesticides. Eur J Epidemiol. 2011 Jul;26(7):547-55. doi: 10.1007/s10654-011-9574-5. Epub 2011 Apr 20. PubMed PMID: 21505849.  

**More Models for Parkinson’s Disease**  
* [Cooper et al, Science 2006](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1983366/pdf/nihms15898.xml.fixed.pdf) open-access [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/16794039)  
* Cooper AA, Gitler AD, Cashikar A, Haynes CM, Hill KJ, Bhullar B, Liu K, Xu K, Strathearn KE, Liu F, Cao S, Caldwell KA, Caldwell GA, Marsischky G, Kolodner RD, Labaer J, Rochet JC, Bonini NM, Lindquist S. Alpha-synuclein blocks ER-Golgi traffic and Rab1 rescues neuron loss in Parkinson's models. Science. 2006 Jul 21;313(5785):324-8. Epub 2006 Jun 22. PubMed PMID: 16794039; PubMed Central PMCID: PMC1983366.  

