##  Therapeutic approaches: symptom relief (37)

---  


## Therapeutic approaches: protection by small molecules (38)

**Inverse correlation between a person’s history of tobacco use & susceptibility to Parkinson’s disease**  
* [PubMed abstract of  Hernan et al. Ann Neurol, 2002](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/12205639) not open-access  
*  Hernán MA, Takkouche B, Caamaño-Isorna F, Gestal-Otero JJ. A meta-analysis of coffee drinking, cigarette smoking, and the risk of Parkinson's disease. Ann Neurol. 2002 Sep;52(3):276-84. PubMed PMID: 12205639.

* [PubMed abstract of Tanner et al. Neurology 2002](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11865136) not open-access  
* Tanner CM, Goldman SM, Aston DA, Ottman R, Ellenberg J, Mayeux R, Langston JW. Smoking and Parkinson's disease in twins. Neurology. 2002 Feb 26;58(4):581-8. PubMed PMID: 11865136.  

**Nicotine itself is probably a part of smoking’s apparent neuroprotective action**

* [Quik et al. Biochem Pharmacol 2009](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC2815339/pdf/nihms-142026.pdf) open access [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/19433069)  
* Quik M, Huang LZ, Parameswaran N, Bordia T, Campos C, Perez XA. Multiple roles for nicotine in Parkinson's disease. Biochem Pharmacol. 2009 Oct 1;78(7):677-85. doi: 10.1016/j.bcp.2009.05.003. Epub 2009 May 9. Review. PubMed PMID: 19433069; PubMed Central PMCID: PMC2815339.  
  
* [Ryan Br J Pharmacol 2001](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pmc/articles/PMC1572727/)open access [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/11309235)  
* Ryan RE, Ross SA, Drago J, Loiacono RE. Dose-related neuroprotective effects of chronic nicotine in 6-hydroxydopamine treated rats, and loss of
neuroprotection in alpha4 nicotinic receptor subunit knockout mice. Br J Pharmacol. 2001 Apr;132(8):1650-6. PubMed PMID: 11309235; PubMed Central PMCID: PMC1572727.

**What is the Mechanism: for Nicotine’s apparent neuroprotective effect?**
* [copy from Lester Lab of Lester et al., Biological Psychiatry. 2012](http://orphanin.caltech.edu/~lester/world/Reprints%20from%20our%20lab/2012/Lester-BiolPsych-2012.pdf) [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/22771239)  
* Lester HA, Miwa JM, Srinivasan R. Psychiatric drugs bind to classical targets within early exocytotic pathways: therapeutic effects. Biol Psychiatry. 2012 Dec 1;72(11):907-15. doi: 10.1016/j.biopsych.2012.05.020. Epub 2012 Jul 6. PubMed PMID: 22771239. 


**Inside-out and upregulation-based mechanisms**   
* [copy from Lester Lab of  Miwa et al, Neuron 2011](http://orphanin.caltech.edu/~lester/world/Reprints%20from%20our%20lab/2011/Miwa-neuron-2011.pdf) [PubMed abstract](http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/21482353)  
* Miwa JM, Freedman R, Lester HA. Neural systems governed by nicotinic acetylcholine receptors: emerging hypotheses. Neuron. 2011 Apr 14;70(1):20-33. doi: 10.1016/j.neuron.2011.03.014. Review. PubMed PMID: 21482353.
  
